Commands.OriginalText:
Group
    az account lock : Manage Azure subscription level locks.

Commands:
    create : Create a subscription lock.
    delete : Delete a subscription lock.
    list   : List lock information in the subscription.
    show   : Show the details of a subscription lock.
    update : Update a subscription lock.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az account lock"

Group
    az account management-group entities : Entity operations (Management Group and Subscriptions)
    for Management Groups.

Commands:
    list : List all entities for the authenticated user.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az account management-group entities"

Group
    az account management-group hierarchy-settings : Provide operations for hierarchy settings
    defined at the management group level. Settings can only be set on the root Management Group of
    the hierarchy.

Commands:
    create : Create hierarchy settings defined at the Management Group level.
    delete : Delete the hierarchy settings defined at the Management Group level.
    list   : Get all the hierarchy settings defined at the Management Group level.
    update : Update the hierarchy settings defined at the Management Group level.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az account management-group hierarchy-
settings"

Group
    az account management-group subscription : Subscription operations for Management Groups.

Commands:
    add               : Add a subscription to a management group.
    remove            : Remove an existing subscription from a management group.
    show              : Show the details of a subscription under a known management group.
    show-sub-under-mg : Get the subscription under a management group.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az account management-group subscription"

Group
    az account management-group tenant-backfill : Backfill Tenant Subscription Operations for
    Management Groups.

Commands:
    get   : Get the backfill status for a tenant.
    start : Start backfilling subscriptions for a tenant.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az account management-group tenant-backfill"

Group
    az account management-group : Manage Azure Management Groups.

Subgroups:
    entities                : Entity operations (Management Group and Subscriptions) for Management
                              Groups.
    hierarchy-settings      : Provide operations for hierarchy settings defined at the management
                              group level. Settings can only be set on the root Management Group of
                              the hierarchy.
    subscription            : Subscription operations for Management Groups.
    tenant-backfill         : Backfill Tenant Subscription Operations for Management Groups.

Commands:
    check-name-availability : Check if a Management Group Name is Valid.
    create                  : Create a new management group.
    delete                  : Delete an existing management group.
    list                    : List all management groups.
    show                    : Get a specific management group.
    update                  : Update an existing management group.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az account management-group"

Group
    az account : Manage Azure subscription information.

Subgroups:
    lock             : Manage Azure subscription level locks.
    management-group : Manage Azure Management Groups.

Commands:
    clear            : Clear all subscriptions from the CLI's local cache.
    get-access-token : Get a token for utilities to access Azure.
    list             : Get a list of subscriptions for the logged in account. By default, only
                       'Enabled' subscriptions from the current cloud is shown.
    list-locations   : List supported regions for the current subscription.
    set              : Set a subscription to be the current active subscription.
    show             : Get the details of a subscription.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az account"

Group
    az acr agentpool : Manage private Tasks agent pools with Azure Container Registries.
        WARNING: This command group is in preview and under development. Reference and support
        levels: https://aka.ms/CLI_refstatus
Commands:
    create : Create an agent pool for an Azure Container Registry.
    delete : Delete an agent pool.
    list   : List the agent pools for an Azure Container Registry.
    show   : Get the properties of a specified agent pool for an Azure Container Registry.
    update : Update an agent pool for an Azure Container Registry.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az acr agentpool"

Group
    az acr connected-registry permissions : Manage the repository permissions accross multiple
    connected registries. Please see https://aka.ms/acr/connected-registry for more information.
        WARNING: Command group 'acr connected-registry' is in preview and under development.
        Reference and support levels: https://aka.ms/CLI_refstatus
Commands:
    show   : Show the connected registry sync scope map information.
    update : Add and remove repository permissions accross all the necessary connected registry sync
             scope maps.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az acr connected-registry permissions"

Group
    az acr connected-registry : Manage connected registry resources with Azure Container Registries.
        WARNING: This command group is in preview and under development. Reference and support
        levels: https://aka.ms/CLI_refstatus
Subgroups:
    permissions        : Manage the repository permissions accross multiple connected registries.
                         Please see https://aka.ms/acr/connected-registry for more information.

Commands:
    create             : Create a connected registry for an Azure Container Registry.
    deactivate         : Deactivate a connected registry from Azure Container Registry.
    delete             : Delete a connected registry from Azure Container Registry.
    get-settings       : Retrieve information required to activate a connected registry, and creates
                         or rotates the sync token credentials.
    list               : List all the connected registries under the current parent registry.
    list-client-tokens : List all the client tokens associated to a specific connected registries.
    show               : Show connected registry details.
    update             : Update a connected registry for an Azure Container Registry.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az acr connected-registry"

Group
    az acr helm repo : Manage helm chart repositories for Azure Container Registries.
        WARNING: This command group is implicitly deprecated because command group 'acr helm' is
        deprecated and will be removed in a future release. Use 'helm v3' instead.

Commands:
    add : Add a helm chart repository from an Azure Container Registry through the Helm CLI.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az acr helm repo"

Group
    az acr helm : Manage helm charts for Azure Container Registries.
        WARNING: This command group has been deprecated and will be removed in future release. Use
        'helm v3' instead. For more information go to https://aka.ms/acr/helm

Subgroups:
    repo                  : Manage helm chart repositories for Azure Container Registries.

Commands:
    delete                : Delete a helm chart version in an Azure Container Registry.
    install-cli [Preview] : Download and install Helm command-line tool.
    list                  : List all helm charts in an Azure Container Registry.
    push                  : Push a helm chart package to an Azure Container Registry.
    show                  : Describe a helm chart in an Azure Container Registry.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az acr helm"

Group
    az acr manifest : Manage artifact manifests in Azure Container Registries.
        WARNING: This command group is in preview and under development. Reference and support
        levels: https://aka.ms/CLI_refstatus
Commands:
    delete          : Delete a manifest in an Azure Container Registry.
    list            : List the manifests in a repository in an Azure Container Registry.
    list-metadata   : List the metadata of the manifests in a repository in an Azure Container
                      Registry.
    list-referrers  : List the ORAS referrers to a manifest in an Azure Container Registry.
    show            : Get a manifest in an Azure Container Registry.
    show-metadata   : Get the metadata of an artifact in an Azure Container Registry.
    update-metadata : Update the manifest metadata of an artifact in an Azure Container Registry.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az acr manifest"

Group
    az acr network-rule : Manage network rules for Azure Container Registries.

Commands:
    add    : Add a network rule.
    list   : List network rules.
    remove : Remove a network rule.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az acr network-rule"

Group

        WARNING: This command group is in preview and under development. Reference and support
        levels: https://aka.ms/CLI_refstatus
Commands:
    build : Queues a quick build task that builds an app and pushes it into an Azure Container
            Registry.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az acr pack"

Group
    az acr private-endpoint-connection : Manage container registry private endpoint connections.
        To create a private endpoint connection use "az network private-endpoint create". For more
        information see https://aka.ms/acr/private-link.

Commands:
    approve : Approve a private endpoint connection request for a container registry.
    delete  : Delete a private endpoint connection request for a container registry.
    list    : List all private endpoint connections to a container registry.
    reject  : Reject a private endpoint connection request for a container registry.
    show    : Show details of a container registry's private endpoint connection.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az acr private-endpoint-connection"

Group
    az acr private-link-resource : Manage registry private link resources.

Commands:
    list : List the private link resources supported for a registry.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az acr private-link-resource"

Group
    az acr replication : Manage geo-replicated regions of Azure Container Registries.

Commands:
    create : Create a replicated region for an Azure Container Registry.
    delete : Delete a replicated region from an Azure Container Registry.
    list   : List all of the regions for a geo-replicated Azure Container Registry.
    show   : Get the details of a replicated region.
    update : Updates a replication.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az acr replication"

Group
    az acr repository : Manage repositories (image names) for Azure Container Registries.

Commands:
    delete    : Delete a repository or image in an Azure Container Registry.
    list      : List repositories in an Azure Container Registry.
    show      : Get the attributes of a repository or image in an Azure Container Registry.
    show-tags : Show tags for a repository in an Azure Container Registry.
    untag     : Untag an image in an Azure Container Registry.
    update    : Update the attributes of a repository or image in an Azure Container Registry.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az acr repository"

    az acr scope-map : Manage scope access maps for Azure Container Registries.
        WARNING: This command group is in preview and under development. Reference and support

Commands:
    create : Create a scope map for an Azure Container Registry.
    delete : Delete a scope map for an Azure Container Registry.
    list   : List all scope maps for an Azure Container Registry.
    show   : Show details and attributes of a scope map for an Azure Container Registry.
    update : Update a scope map for an Azure Container Registry.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az acr scope-map"

Group
    az acr taskrun : Manage taskruns using Azure Container Registries.
        WARNING: This command group is in preview and under development. Reference and support
        levels: https://aka.ms/CLI_refstatus
Commands:
    delete : Delete a taskrun from an Azure Container Registry.
    list   : List the taskruns for an Azure Container Registry.
    logs   : Show run logs for a particular taskrun.
    show   : Get the properties of a named taskrun for an Azure Container Registry.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az acr taskrun"

Group
    az acr token credential : Manage credentials of a token for an Azure Container Registry.
        WARNING: Command group 'acr token' is in preview and under development. Reference and
        support levels: https://aka.ms/CLI_refstatus
Commands:
    delete   : Delete a token credential.
    generate : Generate or replace one or both passwords of a token for an Azure Container Registry.
               For using token and password to access a container registry, see
               https://aka.ms/acr/repo-permissions.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az acr token credential"

Group
    az acr token : Manage tokens for an Azure Container Registry.
        WARNING: This command group is in preview and under development. Reference and support
        levels: https://aka.ms/CLI_refstatus
Subgroups:
    credential : Manage credentials of a token for an Azure Container Registry.

Commands:
    create     : Create a token associated with a scope map for an Azure Container Registry.
    delete     : Delete a token for an Azure Container Registry.
    list       : List all tokens for an Azure Container Registry.
    show       : Show details and attributes of a token for an Azure Container Registry.
    update     : Update a token (replace associated scope map) for an Azure Container Registry.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az acr token"

Group
    az acr : Manage private registries with Azure Container Registries.

Subgroups:
    agentpool          [Preview] : Manage private Tasks agent pools with Azure Container Registries.
    config                       : Configure policies for Azure Container Registries.
    connected-registry [Preview] : Manage connected registry resources with Azure Container
                                   Registries.
    credential                   : Manage login credentials for Azure Container Registries.
    encryption                   : Manage container registry encryption.
    helm            [Deprecated] : Manage helm charts for Azure Container Registries.
    identity                     : Manage service (managed) identities for a container registry.
    manifest           [Preview] : Manage artifact manifests in Azure Container Registries.
    network-rule                 : Manage network rules for Azure Container Registries.
    pack               [Preview] : Manage Azure Container Registry Tasks that use Cloud Native
                                   Buildpacks.
    private-endpoint-connection  : Manage container registry private endpoint connections.
    private-link-resource        : Manage registry private link resources.
    replication                  : Manage geo-replicated regions of Azure Container Registries.
    repository                   : Manage repositories (image names) for Azure Container Registries.
    scope-map          [Preview] : Manage scope access maps for Azure Container Registries.
    task                         : Manage a collection of steps for building, testing and OS &
                                   Framework patching container images using Azure Container
                                   Registries.
    taskrun            [Preview] : Manage taskruns using Azure Container Registries.
    token              [Preview] : Manage tokens for an Azure Container Registry.
    webhook                      : Manage webhooks for Azure Container Registries.

Commands:
    build                        : Queues a quick build, providing streaming logs for an Azure
                                   Container Registry.
    check-health                 : Gets health information on the environment and optionally a
                                   target registry.
    check-name                   : Checks if an Azure Container Registry name is valid and available
                                   for use.
    create                       : Create an Azure Container Registry.
    delete                       : Deletes an Azure Container Registry.
    import                       : Imports an image to an Azure Container Registry from another
                                   Container Registry. Import removes the need to docker pull,
                                   docker tag, docker push. For larger images consider using `--no-
                                   wait`.
    list                         : Lists all the container registries under the current
                                   subscription.
    login                        : Log in to an Azure Container Registry through the Docker CLI.
    run                          : Queues a quick run providing streamed logs for an Azure Container
                                   Registry.
    show                         : Get the details of an Azure Container Registry.
    show-endpoints               : Display registry endpoints.
    show-usage                   : Get the storage usage for an Azure Container Registry.
    update                       : Update an Azure Container Registry.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az acr"

Group
    az afd origin : Manage origins within the specified origin group.
        Origins are the application servers where Front Door will route your client requests.

        WARNING: Command group 'afd' is in preview and under development. Reference and support

    delete : Deletes an existing origin within an origin group.
    list   : Lists all of the existing origins within an origin group.

    update : Update the settings of the specified AFD origin.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az afd origin"

Subgroups:
    ad-admin                    : Manage a postgres server's Active Directory administrator.
    configuration               : Manage configuration values for a server.
    firewall-rule               : Manage firewall rules for a server.
    key                         : Manage PostgreSQL server keys.
    private-endpoint-connection : Manage PostgreSQL server private endpoint connections.
    private-link-resource       : Manage PostgreSQL server private link resources.
    replica                     : Manage read replicas.
    vnet-rule                   : Manage a server's virtual network rules.

Commands:
    create                      : Create a server.
    delete                      : Delete a server.
    georestore                  : Geo-restore a server from backup.
    list                        : List available servers.
    list-skus                   : List available sku's in the given region.

    show                        : Get the details of a server.
    show-connection-string      : Show the connection strings for a PostgreSQL server database.
    update                      : Update a server.
    wait                        : Wait for server to satisfy certain conditions.

To search AI knowledge base for examples, use: az find "az postgres server"

    az restore-point collection : Manage restore point collection.

    create   : Create the restore point collection. Please refer to https://aka.ms/RestorePoints for
               more details. When updating a restore point collection, only tags may be modified.
    delete   : Delete the restore point collection. This operation will also delete all the
               contained restore points.
    list     : Get the list of restore point collections in a resource group.
    list-all : Get the list of restore point collections in the subscription. Use nextLink property
               in the response to get the next page of restore point collections. Do this till
               nextLink is not null to fetch all the restore point collections.

               met.
